===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|あ|sort=あがる|yomi=k|alt=驤がる}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}, analyzed as a compound of root {{com|ojp|alt1=上が|tr1=aga-|t1=rise|pos1=root form|alt2=る|tr2=-r<sub>u</sub>|t2=suffix applied to root verbs such as the aforementioned one to give intransitivity}}, as a result of {{l|en|transitive}} and {{l|en|intransitive}} verbs splitting into two variants, as {{m|ja|上がる|tr=agaru|pos=intransitive}} had undergone {{m|ja|四段活用|tr=yodan katsuyō|t=quadrigrade conjugation}}, which evolved to {{m|ja|五段活用|tr=godan katsuyō|t=quintigrade conjugation}}, while {{m|ja|上げる|tr=ageru|pos=transitive}} had undergone {{m|ja|下二段活用|tr=shimo nidan katsuyō|t=lower bigrade conjugation}}, which evolved to {{m|ja|下一段活用|tr=shimo ichidan katsuyō|t=lower monograde conjugation}}; ultimately from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*anka-}}.<ref>{{R:ja:Martin 1987}}</ref>

First attested in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720 {{CE}}.<ref>{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|上・揚・挙・騰}}</ref>

